Henry Antes was a German immigrant from Freinsheim, Germany who settled in Pennsylvania in 1720. He became a respected religious and political leader, as well as a wheelwright and millwright. He made significant contributions to architecture, religion, and education in Pennsylvania and North Carolina. He advocated for religious tolerance and worked to resolve disputes between various religious and cultural groups in the diverse colonial landscape.
